name: The Creation of Adam
description:
Finally, the finishing touches
On an already glistening world.
The soulless body of the one
Lay before Him, almost complete.
Face expressionless
Arms faint, legs limp
He admires His newest creation.
He reaches out,
Fingers almost touching,
Any closer will cause a spark.

Should one who will wield such power
Be allowed to live
The twitch of a finger,
A tiny flash of light.
God’s one true image
Rises to life

Jackson Keogh
